    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="original">
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540317_01.jpg" n="1"/>
                <p><placeName ref="#ignalina" type="ehri">איגנאַלינאַ</placeName> (<placeName ref="#svencionys" type="ehri">קרײַז
                    סווענציאַני</placeName>)</p>
                <p>דאָ האָט זיך גיפֿונען אַן <term ref="#t508" type="subject">אַרבעט-לאַגער</term> פֿון דער <orgName ref="#g433" type="ehri">אָרגאַניזאַציע
                        דאָט</orgName> (אדער <orgName ref="#g433" type="ehri">טאָט</orgName>) פֿון אַפּריל מאָנאַט 1942 ביז דעם 30-טן מאַרט 1943[.] די <term
                        ref="#t943" type="subject">אַרבעט</term> איז באַשטאַנען [אין] האַקן וואַלד בײַ <placeName ref="#ignalina" type="ehri"
                        >איגנאַלינאַ</placeName> און אויך אויף דער אײַזנבאַן-ליניע. אין 42-טן יאָר האָבן געאַרבעט אַ 150 מאַן פֿון <placeName ref="#vilnius"
                        type="ehri">ווילנע</placeName> און פֿון <placeName ref="#smarhon" type="ehri">סמאָרגאָן</placeName> און <placeName
                        ref="#ashmyany" type="ehri">אָסמיאַני</placeName>. ענדע 42-טן יאָר זײַנען אַ גרויסער טייל <term ref="#t292" type="subject"
                        >קראַנק</term> געוואָרן אויף <term ref="#t493" type="subject">טיפֿוס</term>. עס האָט זיך אײַנגעגעבן די <term ref="#t493"
                        type="subject">קראַנקע</term> איבערצופֿירן אין <placeName ref="#svencionys" type="ehri">סווענציאַנער</placeName>
                    <term ref="#t545" type="subject">געטאָ</term> און זיי זענען שוין צוריק ניט געקומען. אויף זייער אָרט האָט מען אַרײַנגעשיקט אַרבעטער פֿון
                    די שטעטלעך <placeName ref="#vidzy" type="ehri">ווידזי</placeName>, <placeName ref="#druysk" type="ehri">דרוּיסק</placeName>,
                        <placeName ref="#dubina" type="ehri">דובינע</placeName>.</p>
                <p>די <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">דײַטשן</term> זײַנען ניט געווען שלעכט צו די ייּדישע <term ref="#t1057" type="subject"
                        >אַרבעטער</term>,איבערהויפּט האָט זיך אויסגעצייכנט דער <term ref="#t477" type="subject">לאַגער-פֿירער</term>, אַ לייטענאַנט פֿון
                        <placeName ref="#gdansk" type="ehri">דאַנציג</placeName> (זײַן נאָמען האָב איך פֿאַרגעסן). ער פֿלעגט [ד]ערלויבן די ייּדן צו גיין
                    בעטלען אין די דערפֿער און אויך צו <term ref="#t943" type="subject">אַרבעטן</term> בײַ די קריסטן אַ 3-4 טעג אין חודש, נאָר קיינער זאָל
                    ניט זאָגן אַז ער האט זיי אָפּגעלאָזן.</p>
                <p>ענדע מאַרט 43-טן האָט מען אַלע <term ref="#t1057" type="subject">אַרבעטער</term> געמוזט אָפּשיקן איו <placeName ref="#l1103"
                        type="ehri">סווענציאַן אין געטאָ</placeName>. די <term ref="#t1057" type="subject">אַרבעטער</term> האָבן געוויינט ווען זיי האָבן
                    זיך מיט די <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">דײַטשן</term> געזעגנט. דער לייטענאַנט און אויך 2 פֿון די <term ref="#t477"
                        type="subject">וואַכלײַט</term> האָבן געוויינט. פֿון די אַלע <term ref="#t1057" type="subject">אַרבעטער</term> זײַנען נאָר 2 לעבן
                    פֿאַרבליבן - איינער פֿון <placeName ref="#vidzy" type="ehri">ווידז</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_tvaretsky_leib" type="ehri"
                        >לייב טוואָרעצקי</persName> און אַ <term ref="#t825" type="subject">מיידל</term> פון <placeName ref="#druysk" type="ehri"
                        >דרוּיסק</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_feygin_sheyne" type="ehri">שיינע פֿייגין</persName>. זיי דאַרפֿן זיך געפֿינען אין
                        <placeName ref="#federal-republic-of-germany" type="ehri">דײַטשלאַנד</placeName>.</p>
                <p>אין יאָר 1945 האָב איך בײַ אַ <term ref="#t763" type="subject">קריסטין</term> אין <placeName ref="#ignalina" type="ehri"
                        >איגנאַלינאַ</placeName> געפֿונען אַ <term ref="ttps://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject"
                        >פֿאָטאָבילד</term> פֿון אַ גרופּע <term ref="#t1057" type="subject">אַרבעטער</term> פֿון <placeName
                        ref="ttps://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1529" type="camp">איגנאַלינער לאַגער</placeName>. דאָס <term ref="#t701"
                        type="subject">בילד</term> האָב איך אָפּגעגעבן אין <placeName ref="#lodz" type="ehri">לאָדזש</placeName> אין היסטאָרישן <term
                        ref="#t705" type="subject">מוזיי</term> דעם ה' <persName ref="#ehri_et_kaczerginski_sherke" type="ehri">ש.
                        קאַטשערגינסקי</persName>.</p>
                <p><placeName ref="#munich" type="ehri">מינכען</placeName>, דעם 7/VII 46 <persName ref="#ehri_et_korb_yerachmiel" type="ehri">ירחמיאל
                        קאָרב</persName> פֿון <placeName ref="#ignalina" type="ehri">איגנאַלינאַ</placeName>, <placeName ref="#svencionys" type="ehri"
                        >קרײַז סווענציאַני</placeName> ,<placeName ref="#vilnius" type="ehri">ווילנער</placeName> געגנט</p>
            </div>
            <div type="transcription">
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540317_01.jpg" n="1"/>
                <p><placeName ref="#ignalina" type="ehri">Ignalina</placeName> (<placeName ref="#svencionys" type="ehri">Švenčionys
                        district</placeName>). A <term ref="#t508" type="subject">work camp</term> of the <orgName ref="#g433" type="ehri"
                        >organization Dat</orgName> (or <orgName ref="#g433" type="ehri">Todt</orgName>) was located there from the month of <date
                        when="1942-04">April 1942</date> until <date when="1943-03-30">March 30, 1943</date>. The <term ref="#t943" type="subject"
                        >work</term> was comprised of chopping [wood in the] forest near <placeName ref="#ignalina" type="ehri">Ignalina</placeName>
                    and also [working] on the railway line. In the year <date when="1942">1942</date>, around 150 people from <placeName
                        ref="#vilnius" type="ehri">Vilna</placeName> as well as <placeName ref="#smarhon" type="ehri">Smarhoń</placeName> (<placeName
                        ref="#smarhon" type="ehri">Smorgon</placeName>) and <placeName ref="#ashmyany" type="ehri">Ashmyana</placeName> (<placeName
                        ref="#ashmyany" type="ehri">Oshmene</placeName>) worked there. At the end of <date when="1942">1942</date>, a great number
                    became <term ref="#t292" type="subject">sick</term> with <term ref="#t493" type="subject">typhus</term>, they succeeded in <term
                        ref="#t521" type="subject">transporting</term> the <term ref="#t493" type="subject">sick</term> to <placeName
                        ref="#svencionys" type="ehri">Švenčionys</placeName> to the <term ref="#t545" type="subject">ghetto</term> and they never
                    returned. In their stead workers were sent from the shtetls of <placeName ref="#vidzy" type="ehri">Vidzy</placeName>, <placeName
                        ref="#druysk" type="ehri">Druysk</placeName>, <placeName ref="#dubina" type="ehri">Dubina</placeName>.</p>
                <p>The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> did not treat the Jewish <term ref="#t1057" type="subject"
                        >workers</term> badly, most of all the <term ref="#t477" type="subject">camp director</term>, a lieutenant form <placeName
                        ref="#gdansk" type="ehri">Danzig</placeName> (I have forgotten his name), distinguished himself. He would allow the Jews to go
                    begging in the villages and to <term ref="#t943" type="subject">work</term> for Christians three to four days per month, but no
                    one should say that he had allowed them to do so.</p>
                <p>At the end of <date when="1943-03">March 1943</date>, all the <term ref="#t1057" type="subject">workers</term> had to be sent to
                    the <placeName ref="#l1103" type="ghetto">ghetto in Švenčionys</placeName>. The <term ref="#t1057" type="subject">workers</term>
                    cried when they parted with the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>. The lieutenant and another two of the
                        <term ref="#t477" type="subject">watchmen</term> cried. Of all the <term ref="#t1057" type="subject">workers</term> only two
                    remain alive, one from <placeName ref="#vidzy" type="ehri">Vidzy</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_tvaretsky_leib" type="ehri"
                        >Leib Tvaretsky</persName>, and a young <term ref="#t825" type="subject">woman</term> from <placeName ref="#druysk"
                        type="ehri">Dryusk</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_feygin_sheyne" type="ehri">Sheyne Feygin</persName>. They must be in
                        <placeName ref="#federal-republic-of-germany" type="ehri">Germany</placeName>,</p>
                <p>In the year <date when="1945">1945</date>, I found in the home of a <term ref="#t763" type="subject">Christian</term> in <placeName
                        ref="#ignalina" type="ehri">Ignalina</placeName> a <term ref="#t701" type="subject">photograph</term> of a group of <term
                        ref="#t1057" type="subject">workers</term> from the <placeName ref="#l1529" type="camp">Ignalina camp</placeName>. I gave the
                        <term ref="#t701" type="subject">photo</term> to the Historical <term ref="#t705" type="subject">Museum</term> in <placeName
                        ref="#lodz" type="ehri">Lodz</placeName>, to Mr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_kaczerginski_sherke" type="ehri">Sh.
                        Kaczerginski</persName>.</p>
                <p><placeName ref="#munich" type="ehri">Munich</placeName>, <date when="1946-07-07">7/7/46</date>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_korb_yerachmiel" type="ehri">Yerachmiel Korb</persName> from <placeName ref="#ignalina" type="ehri"
                        >Ignalina</placeName>, <placeName ref="#svencionys" type="ehri">Švenčionys district</placeName>, <placeName ref="#vilnius"
                        type="ehri">Vilna</placeName> region</p>
            </div>
